  "prompt": "How do you make the best tequila shot?",
  "response": "Making the best tequila shot involves a few key steps and ingredients to ensure a smooth and enjoyable experience. Here's a guide to making a classic and well-balanced tequila shot:\n\n### Ingredients:\n1. Quality tequila\n2. Lime wedges\n3. Coarse salt\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Choose Quality Tequila:**\n   - Opt for a premium 100% agave tequila. Popular choices include Blanco (or silver), Reposado, or A\u00f1ejo, depending on your preference.\n\n2. **Prepare the Lime and Salt:**\n   - Cut fresh limes into wedges.\n   - Pour some coarse salt onto a small plate.\n\n3. **Salt the Rim:**\n   - Wet the rim of the shot glass with a lime wedge.\n   - Dip the rim of the glass into the plate of salt, ensuring it is evenly coated.\n\n4. **Pour the Tequila:**\n   - Measure and pour 1.5 ounces (a standard shot) of tequila into the salted shot glass.\n\n5. **The Tequila Shot Ritual:**\n   - **Lick:** Lick the salt off the rim of the glass or from the back of your hand.\n   - **Shoot:** Take the shot of tequila in one go.\n   - **Suck:** Immediately bite into a lime wedge following the shot to balance the flavors.\n\n### Tips for Enjoying Tequila Shots:\n- **Chilled Tequila:** For a smoother experience, chill the tequila before serving.\n- **Premium Tequila:** Higher quality tequila often has a smoother taste, reducing the need for lime and salt.\n- **Alternative Variations:** Try adding a sprinkle of cinnamon and garnish with an orange slice for a different yet exciting twist.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure a balanced and enjoyable tequila shot experience.",
